## Common API Endpoints: Detailed Parameters

### `client.members.list(params)`

List members of a company.

**Required Parameters:**
- `company_id` (string) - The ID of the company to list members for (e.g., `"biz_xxxxxxxxxxxxxx"`)

**Optional Parameters:**
- `after` (string | null) - Cursor for forward pagination
- `before` (string | null) - Cursor for backward pagination
- `first` (integer | null) - Number of elements to return (forward pagination)
- `last` (integer | null) - Number of elements to return (backward pagination)
- `direction` (enum | null) - Sort direction: `"asc"` or `"desc"`
- `order` (enum | null) - Sort by: `"id"`, `"usd_total_spent"`, `"created_at"`, `"joined_at"`, or `"most_recent_action"`
- `created_before` (string<date-time> | null) - Maximum creation date filter (e.g., `"2023-12-01T05:00:00.401Z"`)
- `created_after` (string<date-time> | null) - Minimum creation date filter
- `access_level` (enum | null) - Filter by access level: `"no_access"`, `"admin"`, or `"customer"`
- `access_pass_ids` (string[] | null) - Filter by access pass IDs
- `plan_ids` (string[] | null) - Filter by plan IDs
- `statuses` (enum<string>[] | null) - Filter by member statuses
- `promo_code_ids` (string[] | null) - Filter by promo code IDs
- `most_recent_actions` (enum<string>[] | null) - Filter by most recent actions
- `query` (string | null) - Search by name, username, or email (email requires `member:email:read` permission)

**Example:**
```typescript
// List all members
for await (const member of client.members.list({ 
  company_id: "biz_xxxxxxxxxxxxxx" 
})) {
  console.log(member.user.username, member.access_level);
}

// List only admin members
for await (const member of client.members.list({ 
  company_id: "biz_xxxxxxxxxxxxxx",
  access_level: "admin"
})) {
  console.log(member.user.username);
}

// Search for specific members
for await (const member of client.members.list({ 
  company_id: "biz_xxxxxxxxxxxxxx",
  query: "john@example.com"
})) {
  console.log(member.user.email);
}
```

**Response:** Returns a paginated list of member objects with automatic pagination via async iterator.

**Required Permissions:**
- `member:basic:read`
- `member:email:read` (for email in response)
- `member:phone:read` (for phone in response)

